%N A397507 a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} (binomial(4*n+2*k-3,k) - binomial(4*n+2*k-3,k-1)).
%F A397507 a(n) = A397512(n) - A397515(n).
%F A397507 G.f.: (2-g)/((6-5*g) * (1-g+g^2)) where g = 1+x*g^6 is the g.f. of A002295.
%F A397507 Here and below, binomial(N,k) = 0 for k<0.
%F A397507 This is the special case l=4, m=2, c=0, r=1, s=1 of the following family. For integers l, m, c in Z, and for any constants r and s, define a_{l,m,c,r,s}(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} (r*binomial(l*n+m*k-m-1+c,k) - s*binomial(l*n+m*k-m-1+c,k-1)). A_{l,m,c,r,s}(x) = Sum_{n>=0} a_{l,m,c,r,s}(n)*x^n = t^c*(r+s-s*t)/((l+m-(l+m-1)*t)*(1-t+t^m)), where t = t(x) satisfies t = 1 + x*t^(l+m), equivalently y = x*(1+y)^(l+m) with y=t-1.
%o A397507 (PARI) a(n) = sum(k=0, n, binomial(4*n+2*k-3, k)-binomial(4*n+2*k-3, k-1));
%Y A397507 Cf. A396577, A397508.
%Y A397507 Cf. A397512, A397515.
%Y A397507 Cf. A002295, A333096.
